# Python Coding Standards

## Code Quality
- Type hints on all function signatures and class attributes.
- Google-style docstrings on all public classes and functions.
- No `print()` — use `logging` module.
- No hardcoded paths — use `config.py`.
- Catch specific exceptions, provide user-friendly messages.
- Async for all FastAPI endpoints.

## Architecture
- Follow project structure in `PRD.md` section 2.4.
- Absolute imports only: `from src.core.chunking import ...`.
- One responsibility per module.
- FastAPI dependency injection via `Depends()`.

## Testing
- Test files mirror source: `src/core/foo.py` → `tests/test_core/test_foo.py`.
- Shared fixtures in `conftest.py` (temp dirs, test DB).
- Temp directories for file I/O — no permanent side effects.
- Mock LLM calls; real model for embedding tests with minimal data.
- One assertion/behavior per test function.
- Descriptive test names: `test_paragraph_chunking_produces_correct_overlap`.
